Midgaard is the central trade hub of the continent, located at the convergence of major routes.
North leads to the Great Northern Forest and onward to Kowloon's delta ports.
West via Roc Road connects to Kiess (built on fallen Evermeet's ruins).
East runs desert caravan routes to the oasis settlements near the ancient pyramids.
The city grew from practical necessity at a dangerous crossroads, not from ideology or conquest.
Governance evolved through five eras: militia compacts, civic reforms, occult oversight, wartime emergency law, and modern factional tension.
Two factions dominate current politics: the Continuity Faction (preserve existing systems) and the Reckoning Faction (expose buried records and revise old compacts).
Trade ledgers contain entries recording condemned debtors transferred to the Spirebound Conclave in the Cinderteeth Mountains.
Key institutions: the Magistrate Ledgerhouse (civic order), Temple of the Resounding Heart (collective penance), and Guard Command (defense).
Three civic oaths bind public servants: Oath of Light, Oath of the Counted Step, Oath of the Kept Record.
Midgaard endures because of its geographic centrality, not moral authority.
